NNEWI  – Drug peddlers operating be­tween Nnewi and Nnobi, in Anambra State have beaten a man to stupor for informing the Nigeria Drug Law Enforce­ment Agency (NDLEA) of their nefarious activities in the area. For some time now, the ND­LEA had been chasing after the drug peddlers and their patro­nisers about and they had also arrested some of them in the area. The drug pushers number­ing over 25 persons were said to have beaten the man identified as Ajapa, a chicken garnishee at Nnobi abattoir where they descended on him and knocked him to coma. Orientation: Call-Up-Letters Out On Sunday, COVID-19 Rapid… Ikeja Golden Lions Club Applauded For Touching Lives Of… Sources said the drug ped­dlers accused Ajapa of inviting men of the NDLEA to their bunk and hideout located close to the abattoir, a thing that pro­voked them to anger and made them to beat him as warning to deter him and any other hid­den informants from making the mistake next time. At the time Saturday INDE­PENDENT reached the place, Ajapa had been rescued to the hospital by some good Samar­itans who rushed to the place.